Pham Tien Dat is an Intern AI Engineer specialized in developing and fine-tuning deep learning models, particularly in Computer Vision and Natural Language Processing. With a strong academic background and personal projects, their core expertise lies in architectures such as YOLOv8 for object detection, GPT-4o for language generation, and Support Vector Machine (SVM) for classification, using frameworks like PyTorch, Scikit-learn, and OpenCV. Their experience spans multiple projects, including a RAG-based chatbot for the 2019 Labor Law, where they implemented a hybrid retrieval architecture combining vector-based and keyword-based search, and a video tracking project on the MOT17 dataset, demonstrating proficiency in the full ML pipeline from data preprocessing to model fine-tuning.

Technically, Pham Tien Dat is proficient in Python and has hands-on experience with a range of libraries and frameworks, including NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib, and TorchText. They have also worked with databases like ChromaDB and have experience in techniques such as re-ranking, object detection, multi-object tracking, and temperature sampling. Their domain knowledge extends to image processing, feature extraction, and poem generation, showcasing their ability to apply deep learning concepts to diverse applications. With a strong foundation in computer science and a Bachelor's degree in progress from Ton Duc Thang University, Pham Tien Dat brings a unique combination of theoretical knowledge and practical skills to the table, making them a promising candidate in the field of AI engineering.